==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/laɪm/}}

===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[lim#Old English|līm]]''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[lijm]]'', German ''[[Leim]]''; Latin ''[[limus]]'' ‘mud’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# ''(poetic)'' any gluey or adhesive substance; something which traps or captures someone
# {{mineralogy}} A white alkaline substance, calcium oxide, obtained from [[limestone]]; [[quicklime]]
#:*'''1952''': '''Lime''', which is the product of the burning of chalk or limestone, might be bought ready burnt, or it could be burnt in kilns specially constructed in the neighbourhood of the building operations. &mdash; L.F. Salzman, ''Building in England'', page 149.
# A dry white powder (calcium hydroxide).

